metadata.name: SEARCH
metadata.description:
From the minute I was exposed to the other world - "Social Media" , I felt a longing to be found as if I had deep dived into a different realm.  
As an artist, this feeling held me back. The moment I felt like wanting to be recognized or "found" It constantly drew me away from my creative process. 
Countless burnouts have led me here and now I've found a greater meaning in being an artist than just recognition.

Soul searching for me is self reflection, Welcome.

"Search"  A self portrait by Taksh Shikari.
